message.content: February has 28 days, thus Suzanne can walk $\dfrac{28}{3}=\boxed{9\frac{1}{3}}$ groups of "every third day." Although Suzanne can't walk $\frac13$ of a mile, she must walk at least $9$ miles, and the next "every third day" would require her to walk the leftover distance to $12$ miles.
